The paper discusses Knowledge Compilation (KC) which is a subfield of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) that deals with the compilation of boolean functions into a more efficient representation. The paper also mentions the use of CNF (Conjunctive Normal Form) which is a common representation in logic and automated reasoning, placing it in the subfield of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the hierarchy of classes UC_k, WC_k, and PC_k, which are related to computational complexity and decision problems, placing it in the subfields of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
